The Organisation Undoing Tax Abuse and the SA Pilots Association brought the case accusing her of mismanagement during her 5-year stint chairing the board. Judge Ronel Tolmay referred the case to the NPA for possible further investigation. Myeni has been ordered to pay Outa and SAAPA's legal costs. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former South African Airways chairperson Dudu Myeni has been declared a delinquent director for life. This means Myeni cannot hold any directorship in any company for the rest of her life. Organisation Undoing Tax Abuse (OUTA) and the SAA Pilots' Association (SAAPA) brought forward the case to court. READ: Myeni refutes damning evidence by SAA's former CCO They accuse Myeni of plunging the national carrier into financial chaos while she was chairperson. The judgment has been referred to the National Prosecution Authority for possible further investigations. Myeni is also expected to pay costs. Former SAA chairperson Dudu Myeni has been declared a delinquent director for life. Courtesy #DStv403